MEC Nandi Mayathula-Khoza says the regulations will be amended because of the high level of deaths. JOHANNESBURG - The Gauteng Social Development Department says it will be reviewing initiation school laws as the season approaches. MEC Nandi Mayathula-Khoza says the regulations will be amended because of the high level of deaths. Earlier this year, the CRL Rights Commission revealed that over 250 young men died during initiation season in six provinces, including Gauteng. The MEC's spokesperson Mbangwa Xaba said: It's in terms of terms of protecting children under the age of 16, so that they re not exposed to child neglect, abduction and abuse. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)